{{Infobox person | name = Rachel Chagall | image = | caption = | birth_name = Rachel Levin | yearsactive = 1987â2006 | birth_date = {{birth date and age|1956|11|24}} | birth_place = [[New York City]], [[New York]], U.S. | occupation = Actress }} '''Rachel Chagall''' (born November 24, 1956) is an [[United States|American]] [[actress]], who specialized in comedic roles. She best known for roles as Gaby on the film ''[[Gaby: A True Story]]'' (1987), , for which she was nominated for [[Golden Globe Award for Best Actress â Motion Picture Drama]] , and as [[Val Toriello]] on ''[[The Nanny (TV series)|The Nanny]]'' (1993â1999).
== Life and career == Born as '''Rachel Levin''', she selected the name Rachel Chagall as there was already another Rachel Levin in the industry. She is perhaps best known for her role as the dimwitted sidekick, [[Val Toriello|"Val"]], on the 1990s [[United States|American]] television series ''[[The Nanny (TV series)|The Nanny]]'', alongside her longtime friend [[Fran Drescher]]. The last name Toriello she took on the show was the last name of one of Fran's cousins.
She made guest appearances on ''[[Just Shoot Me!]]'' and ''[[Strong Medicine]]''. She also played a mysterious woman in the show ''[[What I Like About You (TV series)|What I Like About You]]''. Under her birth name (Rachel Levin), Chagall appeared in ''[[Gaby: A True Story]]'' (1987) in the title role as [[Gabriela Brimmer]] (for which she was nominated for a [[Golden Globe]] - Best Actress in a Motion Picture - Drama)<ref>[http://www.imdb.com/name/nm0149575/awards Awards for Rachel Chagall ]</ref> and ''[[White Palace (film)|White Palace]]'' (1990) in the role of Rachel. She also appeared in ''[[The Last Supper (1995 film)|The Last Supper]]'' (1995).
On December 6, 2004, Chagall appeared at the cast reunion for ''[[The Nanny (TV series)|The Nanny]]'', called ''[[The Nanny Reunion: A Nosh to Remember]]''. Since 2006 she has not done television roles.<ref>[http://www.imdb.com/name/nm0149575/ Filmography by type for Rachel Chagall ]</ref>
